com.camerontec.util.datamodel.fix

Class CachingUTCDateTimeEncoder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.datamodel.fix.AbstractUTCEncoder
      • com.camerontec.util.datamodel.fix.CachingUTCDateTimeEncoder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NanosEncoder

    public final class CachingUTCDateTimeEncoder
extends AbstractUTCEncoder
    Encoder of nanoseconds into a UTC date and time format which caches previous encodings for reuse when possible to avoid redundant encodings.

    The caching algorithm is simple:

    • Timestamp each cache update in seconds
    • If a new encoding is requested in the same second, only the higher precision components are encoded. The remainder are copied from the previously cached value.

    • Method Detail

      • getCachedDateTime

        public byte[] getCachedDateTime()
        Return the cached date time.

        Note that direct access to the internal cache is provided for performance only. The caller should never modify the returned value in any way.

        Returns:
        The cached date time. The length of the cache depends on the precision selected during construction. If the cache has not yet been initialised it is guaranteed to be filled with '0' bytes.
        See Also:
        encodeNanosInternally(long)

      • encodeNanosInternally

        public byte[] encodeNanosInternally(long nanosSinceEpoch)
        Encode the nanoseconds offset from the Epoch to the internal cache only.

        Note that System.nanoTime() DOES NOT guarantee to return nanoseconds from the Epoch. Use WallClock.nanoTime() instead for this purpose.

        Parameters:
        nanosSinceEpoch - The nanoseconds offset from the Epoch.
        Returns:
        The internal cache.
        See Also:
        getCachedDateTime()
